A.R.8.3.2:M4_M2 { @ Risk_Floating_net space to Mn (from M1 to Mtop) [connects to OD] < 0.5 um, >= 0.23 um is not allowed Definition: 1. Risk_Floating_net: cumulative floating metal and VIA top area [cumulative area > 2.20E+06 um2, from M1 to top metal and VIA1 to top VIA, and doesn't connect to OD] 2. floating metal and VIA: metal and VIA doesn't connect to OD This rule is checked by the cumulative connections (from M1 to top metal and VIA1 to top VIA respectively)   
   M2_wi_DIO = NET AREA RATIO M2 SD > 0 [!!AREA(SD)]
   M2_CHK1 = M2 INTERACT (NET AREA RATIO M4 VIA3 SD IMD_M2_M2_A > A_R_8_3_2_A ACCUMULATE ACC_M3_M2_A [!AREA(SD)*(AREA(M4)+AREA(VIA3))])
   M2_CHK3 = NET AREA RATIO M2_CHK1 M4 > 0

   E = EXT [M2_CHK3] M2_wi_DIO >= A_R_8_3_2_S2 < A_R_8_3_2_S1 ABUT < 90 // NOT CONNECTED
