   NET AREA RATIO M4 VIA3 SD M2_CHK2 > A_R_8_3_2_A ACCUMULATE ACC_M3_M2_A [!!AREA(M2_CHK2)*!AREA(SD)*(AREA(M4)+AREA(VIA3))] RDB ONLY A.R.8.3.2:M4_M2.rep M4 VIA3 M2_CHK2 BY LAYER
}


ACC_M4_M1_A = NET AREA RATIO M4 VIA3 SD IMD_M1_M1_A > 0 ACCUMULATE ACC_M3_M1_A [!AREA(SD)*(AREA(M4)+AREA(VIA3))]
A.R.8.3:M4_M1 { @ Risk_Floating_net space to Mn (from M1 to Mtop) [connects to OD] < 0.17 um, >= 0.05 um is not allowed Definition: 1. Risk_Floating_net: cumulative floating metal and VIA top area [cumulative area > 7.50E+05 um2, from M1 to top metal and VIA1 to top VIA, and doesn't connect to OD] 2. floating metal and VIA: metal and VIA doesn't connect to OD This rule is checked by the cumulative connections (from M1 to top metal and VIA1 to top VIA respectively)   
